## Abstract

We propose a computational and mythic-archetypal model of moral transformation based on stochastic gradient dynamics in a redemption potential landscape. The MODAC framework interprets classical ‚Äúfallen, tested, redeemed‚Äù narratives as dynamical escape processes from pride-based attractor basins into unity-aligned basins, governed by micro-correction dynamics and noisy grace perturbations. Rather than moral purity, MODAC asserts **directionality** (positive derivative over time) as the fundamental marker of transformation.

-----

